headline: Why The Nasdaq (NDAQ) Story Is Shifting As Analyst Targets Cluster Above US$110
summary: The fair value price target for Nasdaq has been nudged lower from US$108.33 to US$107.73, a small adjustment that still sits close to where many analysts now cluster in the low to mid US$110s. Even as the consolidated Street target edges down slightly, several firms are lifting individual targets into the US$113 to US$120 range and keeping positive ratings in place. As you read on, you will see how these cross currents shape the evolving analyst story and what to watch as new research comes...
